<ul style="list-style-type:disc; margin-left:36px">
<li><span style="font-size:14px"><span style="font-family:Lucida Sans Unicode,Lucida Grande,sans-serif"><strong>Shekatkar Committee</strong> recommended creation of 3 integrated theatre commands</span></span>
<ol style="list-style-type:lower-roman; margin-left:36px">
<li value="1"><span style="font-size:14px"><span style="font-family:Lucida Sans Unicode,Lucida Grande,sans-serif">Northern Command for China Border</span></span></li>
<li><span style="font-size:14px"><span style="font-family:Lucida Sans Unicode,Lucida Grande,sans-serif">Western Command for Pakistan Border</span></span></li>
<li><span style="font-size:14px"><span style="font-family:Lucida Sans Unicode,Lucida Grande,sans-serif">Southern Command for the maritime borders</span></span></li></ol></li>
<li><span style="font-size:14px"><span style="font-family:Lucida Sans Unicode,Lucida Grande,sans-serif">The Indian armed forces currently have 17 commands (7 army, 3 navy and 7 Air force).</span></span></li>
<li><span style="font-size:14px"><span style="font-family:Lucida Sans Unicode,Lucida Grande,sans-serif">During war, coordination of operations is expected to be carried out at the level of Service headquarters through the Chiefs of Staff Committee. The chairman of COSC is still not appointed</span></span></li>
<li><span style="font-size:14px"><span style="font-family:Lucida Sans Unicode,Lucida Grande,sans-serif">What is ITC? Itâ€™s a unified command of the three services, under a single commander, for geographical theaters that are of security concern. Commander will execute operational plans. It will enhance efficacy and efficiency against the enemy.</span></span>
<ul style="list-style-type:circle; margin-left:36px">
<li><span style="font-size:14px"><span style="font-family:Lucida Sans Unicode,Lucida Grande,sans-serif">Avoids duplication, economy of resources and ensures optimum utilization of available resources</span></span></li>
<li><span style="font-size:14px"><span style="font-family:Lucida Sans Unicode,Lucida Grande,sans-serif">Nations like US and China have integrated theatre. The Indian border along Chinese side has a single command.</span></span></li>
<li><span style="font-size:14px"><span style="font-family:Lucida Sans Unicode,Lucida Grande,sans-serif">COSC, during war times, functions on the principle of consensus. This delays operational activity.</span></span></li></ul></li>
<li><span style="font-size:14px"><span style="font-family:Lucida Sans Unicode,Lucida Grande,sans-serif">Argument against- </span></span>
<ul style="list-style-type:circle; margin-left:36px">
<li><span style="font-size:14px"><span style="font-family:Lucida Sans Unicode,Lucida Grande,sans-serif">India is geographically not large enough and resources from one theatre can be easily moved to another theatre</span></span></li>
<li><span style="font-size:14px"><span style="font-family:Lucida Sans Unicode,Lucida Grande,sans-serif">Division of already scarce resources is infeasible</span></span></li></ul></li></ul>
